commit.message: Bump version, update META.*

Fix Perl 5.8 compatibility

Remove use of //
Update Changes, update META.*, bump version

Always run tests for both reference implementations, even if one is missing

XML::LibXML or HTML::TreeBuilder::XPath, we take both
Add a test for :last-of-type
Note that :contains does not exist in the spec ...

Properly implement first-of-type, nth-of-type

Also fix test case for nth-of-type()
Generalize child selector to allow for arbitrary node names

Test with XML::LibXML in addition to HTML::TreeBuilder

Normalize nodes, for consistency between HTML::TreeBuilder and XML::LibXML testing

Output more debuggging information when failing

Fix HTML semantics to be amenable to LibXML
cannot be contained in a

tag ...

Split out the parsing of pseudo-selectors, An+B

This allows us to parse things in better granularity. Especially
for allowing whitespace and more complex formulae.
Clean whitespace
Bump version, update Changes, META.*
Whitespace cleanup

Fix typo in documentation

This addresses RT #140473 , reported by JDEGUEST
Bump version, update Changes

Add support for compiling :disabled, :selected, :checked, :text, :last-of-type

I'm not sure whether the Perl XPath libaries support this, but at least
we can compile it.

This addresses RT #124406, thanks to Andrew Maguire
Add explicit Perl version of 5.008 to metadata
Bump version, update Changes

Fix test/build prerequisites, regenerate META.*

This addresses RT 127555, reported by Dan Book, thanks!
Make Makefile.PL callable/loadable as module
Add author tests
New date format

Change skipping for HTML::TreeBuilder::XPath

It seems that 5.25.x doesn't set $@ in our current case when
HTML::TreeBuilder::XPath can't be loaded. Let's hope that the return
value from eval{} is still undef.
Fix release date...

Switch to CPAN META spec 2

Hopefully, this resolves the bug where metacpan is not recognizing new
versions. Most likely this was caused by having a 'provides' key but
no corresponding version...
Add (very basic) prerequisites
Also add the release date in yyyymmdd format
Add Changes for 0.22, no need to upgrade
Add author test for an update to the Changes file
